# Software Development Workflow

## Purpose
Workflow for systematic management of software development processes with anchor document as strategic foundation

## Workflow Overview
Entire software development lifecycle management from anchor document creation through deployment, with anchor document serving as the primary strategic reference for all subsequent stages

## Workflow Stages

### 1. Anchor Document Creation
- **Responsible**: PM Agent, Developer Agent
- **Input**: Business concept, initial requirements
- **Output**: Project anchor document
- **Template**: `.ai/templates/anchor_template.md`
- **Deliverable**: `docs/dev/anchor/anchor_<project>_<version>.md` (version information managed in Meta section)
- **Purpose**: Establish strategic foundation and comprehensive project planning

### 2. Requirements Analysis
- **Responsible**: PM Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, business requirements, market research results
- **Output**: Product requirements document (PRD)
- **Template**: `.ai/templates/prd_template.md`
- **Deliverable**: `docs/dev/PRD/prd_<product>.md` (version information managed in Meta section)

### 3. Architecture Design
- **Responsible**: Developer Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, product requirements document
- **Output**: System architecture document
- **Template**: `.ai/templates/architecture_template.md`
- **Deliverable**: `docs/dev/archi/architecture_<project>.md` (version information managed in Meta section)

### 4. Feature Specification
- **Responsible**: Developer Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, architecture document, product requirements
- **Output**: Feature specification document (including APIs)
- **Template**: `.ai/templates/spec_template.md`
- **Deliverable**: `docs/dev/spec/spec_<module>.md` (version information managed in Meta section)

### 5. Technical Decision Making
- **Responsible**: Developer Agent, PM Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, architecture, specification, constraint conditions
- **Output**: Technical decision making record
- **Template**: `.ai/templates/decision_template.md`
- **Deliverable**: `docs/dev/decision/decision_<topic>_<date>.md`

### 6. Development Implementation
- **Responsible**: Developer Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, feature specification document, architecture document
- **Output**: Source code, unit tests
- **Verification**: Code review, quality assurance

### 7. Testing and Verification
- **Responsible**: Developer Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, implemented code, test cases
- **Output**: Test results, bug reports
- **Verification**: Integration testing, user acceptance testing

### 8. Deployment and Operations
- **Responsible**: Developer Agent
- **Input**: Anchor document, verified code, deployment plan
- **Output**: Deployed system, operations documentation
- **Verification**: Post-deployment testing, monitoring

## Agent Roles

### PM Agent
- Anchor document creation & strategic planning
- Product requirements definition & priority setting
- Stakeholder communication & expectation management
- Product roadmap management & progress tracking
- **L1/L2 Role**: Can serve as L1 author for anchor and PRD documents, L2 reviewer for product quality

### Developer Agent
- Anchor document technical contributions
- Technical architecture design
- Feature specification & API design
- Code development & quality assurance
- Deployment & operations support
- **L1 Role**: Primary author for technical documents
- **L2 Role**: Senior reviewer for code quality and architecture

### Finance Agent (Optional)
- Development cost budget analysis
- ROI evaluation & financial feasibility verification
- Resource allocation optimization proposals
- **L1/L2 Role**: Can serve as L1 author for financial documents, L2 reviewer for development ROI

## L1/L2 Role Definitions

### L1 Agent (Author) Responsibilities
- Document creation and initial development
- Basic quality assurance and self-review
- Submission for L2 review process
- **Meta Field**: Author field assignment

### L2 Agent (Reviewer) Responsibilities
- Senior-level work review and validation
- Technical excellence assessment
- Final approval and certification
- **Meta Field**: Reviewer field assignment

